    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-06-22T17:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-06-22T17:34:00-05:00" n="625"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName> files, lot 53 D 413:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of Staff, United States Army (<persName
                            corresp="#p_CGJL1" type="from">Collins</persName>) to the Commander in
                        Chief Far East (<persName corresp="#p_CGMW1" type="to"
                        >Clark</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>operational immediate</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-06-22T18:34:00-04:00"
                            >June 22, 1953—6:34 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_DA1">DA</gloss> 942047. From <gloss target="#t_CSUSA1"
                        >CSUSA</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>. This is a
                    joint State–Defense message. Reur message DTG 221100Z from Hq ArmyEight.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d625fn1">Dated June 22, <ref target="#pg_1231">p.
                        1231</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Believe that you should make no commitment to <persName corresp="#p_RS1"
                        >Rhee</persName> at your next meeting on suggestions for changes in <gloss
                        target="#t_POWs1">POW</gloss> agreement contained in para 5<hi rend="italic"
                        >d</hi> of reference message but listen to what he has to say. In general
                    believe <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> should not be encouraged to
                    think we are prepared to renegotiate armistice agreement. However, we are
                    interested in <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName>’s reaction to your
                    suggestion. Suggest you submit summary of <persName corresp="#p_RS1"
                        >Rhee</persName>’s reaction and follow up with such additional comments as
                    result from discussion of this and other aspects of situation with <persName
                        corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_CGJL1"
                        >Collins</persName>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
